the voice of palestinian civil society a call for non violent resistance events at stanford the voice of palestinian civil society a call for non violent resistance facebook twitter email print add to calendar students for palestinian equal rights is teaming up with the speakers bureau arab student association at stanford arab studies table and muslim students awareness network to host one of the most prominent palestinian non violent resistance leaders in the palestinian struggle for self determination dr mustafa barghouti barghouti graduated from stanford graduate school of business in 1995 co founded the palestinian national initiative and the union of palestinian medical relief committees he also came in second place in the 2006 palestinian national authority presidential race and was nominated for a nobel peace prize for his efforts in promoting peace in the middle east conflict barghouti will be discussing how non violent resistance is the best way for palestinians to achieve self determination equal rights and security here is an op ed he wrote on the subject http www nytimes com 2012 02 22 opinion peaceful protest can free palestine html when monday march 5 2012 7 00 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where cubberley auditorium map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags lecture reading international humanities health wellness public service sponsor students for palestinian equal rights contact 4062509432 jdschott stanford edu admission everyone is welcome permalink http events stanford edu events 313 31363 more info last modified march 5 2012
